Find sources: "Mason Morfit" – news · newspapers · books · scholar · JSTOR (September 2014) (Learn how and when to remove this template message)




(Learn how and when to remove this template message)


G. Mason Morfit president of ValueAct Capital. He was appointed to the Board of Directors of Microsoft in March-2014.[1][2]



Contents


1 Education
2 Career
3 Miscellaneous
4 References



Education[edit]
Morfit has a B.A. from Princeton University and he is a CFA charter holder. [clarification needed]
Career[edit]
Morfit joined the ValueAct Capital in January 2001. Prior to that he worked in equity research for Credit Suisse First Boston. He is a director of Valeant Pharmaceuticals International and a former director of Advanced Medical Optics, Inc., C.R. Bard, Inc., Immucor, Inc., MSD Performance, Inc. and Solexa, Inc.[3]
Miscellaneous[edit]
In December 2016, Morfit catalyzed a tribute to Carrie Fisher at Lucasfilm Yoda statue by dropping a bouquet of flowers and a personal note. The site became a citywide meeting point for grieving Star Wars fans.[4]
References[edit]


^ Profile, valuewalk.com; accessed September 22, 2014.
^ Profile, softpedia.com; accessed September 22, 2014.
^ Profile, valueact.com; accessed September 22, 2014.
^ [1], sfgate.com; accessed January 5, 2016.








